d less on specific literary borrowing, and more on shared familiarity with cultural discourses involving the legitimating portrayal of new cults in the ancient world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aApostelgeschichte /Text. 4aEpiphanie. 4aGefangenenbefreiung. 4aZeithintergrund. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311018266840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091561740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110915617423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110915617/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014